Erdogan Sets 12-Year Goals in Turkey Re-Election, Sabah Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-03T05:59:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/erdogan-sets-12-year-goals-in-turkey-re-election-sabah-says.html
Turkish Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip
Erdogan  is setting 12-year economic goals in his manifesto for
re-election this year, Sabah newspaper reported.  The economic targets for 2023, the 100th anniversary of the
foundation of the Turkish Republic, include more than halving
the jobless rate to 5 percent and doubling gross domestic
product per capital to $25,000, the newspaper reported from
Ankara.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
